cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision algorithms for object detection in images captured by UAVs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning and neural networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The application of these algorithms to UAVs suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category. Finally, the use of attention and memory mechanisms in the proposed approach suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as well.
